&lt;p&gt;AfC 3070a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Band 6 - Data Quality Service Support Manager - Fixed Term to 31/03/2021&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Quality Department are seeking to recruit a full time (37.5 hours) highly motivated and enthusiastic Data Quality Service Support Manager to join our team on a Fixed Term contract until the 31st March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has initiated a programme of work aimed at improving and modernising its Patient Administration System (PAS) which is used to manage patient pathways for elective treatment and outpatient clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of this programme you will be progressing various spin-off initiatives that are all aimed atimproving standardization of how the PAS system is used across the Trust, and to deliver significant data quality improvements underpinning performance and patient care. Activities will range from problem solving and analysis for identifying solution options though to hands-on delivery of process definition and data maintenance tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be able to demonstrate excellent communication and negotiation skills; times when they have made a real difference in the workplace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have an excellent record of delivering work to strict deadlines while meeting mandatory quality requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have ability to continuously improve performance by providing effective solutions to potentially complex problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like you then we would welcome your application!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time fixed term post 37.5 hours a week Monday - Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust’s main hospital sites are St James’ Hospital and the Leeds General Infirmary. The post holder’s work base will be St James’ Hospital. Both of the main sites have excellent transport links to Leeds and West Yorkshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For all enquiries, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Gregson, Programme Manager, Digital Maturity&lt;/p&gt;
